div.p:
Mr. Churchill observed that the plan as prepared would result in some confusion;
                    that a fact to be given consideration was the delay of shipments to Russia; that
                    the Russians would undoubtedly be disappointed.

Mr. Churchill observed that the fighting in the Far East and the fighting the Russians are doing should take priority over other things;
that Magnet and the Iceland relief are secondary. That he was sorry about reducing
Magnet , but he could understand the necessity therefor.
